## 3. Problem Statement

India has 1,000+ central schemes and hundreds of state-level schemes. Most eligible citizens — farmers, students, women, elderly — never claim them. The government's own discovery portal, myScheme.gov.in, fails in four structural ways: rigid 12-question form with no conversational flexibility, keyword-only matching (no semantic reasoning), no memory of returning citizens, and entirely reactive — it never tells a citizen about new relevant schemes.

Research on PM-JAY confirms that low awareness of one's own eligibility — not absence of schemes — is the primary barrier to uptake, and it disproportionately affects the poorest citizens who need the schemes most.

**The opportunity:** A conversational, memory-enabled, proactively-acting agent that validates eligibility rigorously, grounds claims in official sources, and reaches citizens when new schemes appear — addressing all four failure modes of myScheme with a genuinely novel architecture.

