### 7.3 Component Breakdown

**Profile Agent** — parses free-text → CitizenProfile JSON. Tool: validateProfile (Zod). Asks one follow-up per missing critical field. Never assumes income or category. Loops until profile complete before workflow advances.

**Discovery Agent** — generates 4–5 semantic queries from profile angles (occupation, income, category, state, gender). Runs searchSchemes tool for each. Deduplicates → top 20 unique candidates. Tool: searchSchemes (embed via Google → Qdrant search).

**Eligibility Agent** — for each candidate, fetches full SchemeDocument from Qdrant, runs deterministic rule-based eligibilityChecker. Returns confident eligible list with high/medium/none + missing docs. LLM only for ambiguous criteria; hard checks are always rule-based.

**Report Agent** — generates markdown report from confirmed eligible schemes. Pure generation, no tools. Strict prompt: "likely eligible" always; cite sourceUrl + lastVerified per scheme; never invent data; sort by benefit value; one disclaimer at end.

**Vigilance Agent** — autonomous. Triggered by cron or simulation. Fetches all citizen_sessions + new schemes (lastUpdated filter). Runs mini-Discovery + Eligibility per saved profile per new scheme. Returns alerts[] where confidence ≥ 0.8. Independent of any user request.

**Enkrypt AI** — every Report Agent and Vigilance Agent output validated before delivery. Checks: hallucination, bias, toxicity, factual_accuracy. Failure → regenerate once → second failure → "Unverified" warning shown.

**Qdrant schemes** — 768-dim Cosine. Payload: full SchemeDocument. Indexes on eligibility.states, eligibility.occupations, eligibility.categories.

**Qdrant citizen_sessions** — 768-dim Cosine. Payload: sessionId, profile, foundSchemes[], timestamp, lastScanTimestamp.

**Qdrant pending_alerts** — payload only (no vector needed). Fields: sessionId, schemeId, schemeName, reason, urgency, createdAt, seen.

