### 7.5 Technical Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Reason | Trade-off |
|---|---|---|
| OpenRouter auto-router for reasoning | Token exhaustion on single provider mid-sprint; auto-router handles outages | Nondeterministic model selection; verify morning of demo |
| Google for embeddings only | Embedding calls far fewer than reasoning calls; separate + more generous quota | Requires 2 API keys instead of 1 |
| Next.js API routes as backend | Single Vercel deployment; no separate Express server | 10s/30s timeout risk; must test on Vercel on Day 6 |
| Static JSON for scheme data | Verifiable, git-controlled, no scraping legal risk | Data staleness; mitigated by lastVerified field |
| Qdrant Cloud (not local) | Mandatory; 1GB free; accessible from Vercel serverless | Cold start latency; pre-warm before demo |
| Rule-based eligibility (not LLM) | Deterministic and auditable for binary criteria | More code to write; far more reliable |
| Vercel Cron for Vigilance | Free; one-line vercel.json config | Only runs in production, not localhost |
| TypeScript only | Hackathon theme "No Python. No Excuses."; Mastra is TypeScript-native | No Python ML libraries available |
| **LLM Observability via Langfuse** | Judges flagged "complete absence of LLM observability" as critical gap (Industry score: 6.25/10). Langfuse traces every agent step, token count, and latency with zero infrastructure cost on free tier | Adds one npm package + LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY/SECRET env vars; minimal overhead per request |
| **Vigilance Agent decoupling (post-hackathon)** | Current Next.js monolith couples Vigilance Agent to the same serverless runtime as the UI — prevents independent scaling. Feedback: decouple into independent serverless function triggered via event bridge | For hackathon demo: Vercel Cron is sufficient. Production: migrate to separate Vercel function or RabbitMQ-triggered worker |
| **Upstash Redis rate limiting** | Feedback flagged lack of API rate limiting as a security gap. Upstash Redis provides serverless, pay-per-use rate limiting compatible with Vercel Edge — no dedicated Redis server required | Adds UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL + UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN env vars; requires @upstash/ratelimit package |
| **GDPR/DPDP right-to-erasure** | Persistent citizen sessions in Qdrant constitute personal data under India's DPDP Act 2023 and GDPR. A delete endpoint is required for compliance | Simple Qdrant delete-by-ID call; no complex data mapping required |
| **CRISPE prompt framework** | Feedback: prompts lack few-shot examples, personality constraints, and explicit temperature/max_tokens. CRISPE (Capacity, Role, Insight, Statement, Personality, Experiment) improves output determinism and quality | Longer system prompts; more tokens per request; mitigated by using temperature:0 for deterministic agents |

