### 8.6 Authentication, Authorization, Rate Limiting, and Data Governance

> **Feedback addressed:** HiDevs judges scored Industry at 6.25/10 due to "lack of API security (authentication, rate limiting) and GDPR-compliant data governance (right to erasure)." All four gaps are addressed below — split by hackathon MVP and production plan.

#### Hackathon MVP: Anonymous Session IDs
- Client generates UUID on first visit via `crypto.randomUUID()`
- Stored in localStorage as `schemeseva_session_id`
- Passed with every API call as `sessionId`
- Qdrant stores and retrieves by this ID
- Risk: low for MVP (no financial transactions, no PII beyond self-reported profile)

```typescript
// src/lib/session.ts
export function getOrCreateSessionId(): string {
  if (typeof window === 'undefined') return 'ssr-placeholder';
  const key = 'schemeseva_session_id';
  let id = localStorage.getItem(key);
  if (!id) { id = crypto.randomUUID(); localStorage.setItem(key, id); }
  return id;
}
export function clearSession(): void {
  if (typeof window !== 'undefined') localStorage.removeItem('schemeseva_session_id');
}
```

#### Rate Limiting — Upstash Redis (add on Day 4)

Rate limiting prevents abuse of the expensive agent pipeline. Upstash Redis is serverless, free-tier, and works natively with Vercel Edge.

