### 8.7 AI/ML Layer Documentation

> **Feedback addressed:** Judges flagged "prompts lack explicit few-shot examples, personality constraints, and experiment parameters." All agents below now use the CRISPE framework and include temperature/max_tokens. Temperature is set to 0 for deterministic agents (Eligibility, Vigilance) and 0.3 for generative agents (Report, Profile).

**CRISPE Framework used for all prompts:**
- **C**apacity — what role/expertise the model takes on
- **R**ole — the specific persona
- **I**nsight — relevant context and constraints
- **S**tatement — the exact task
- **P**ersonality — tone and style constraints
- **E**xperiment — output format specification

**Model configuration with temperature and token settings:**
```typescript
// src/lib/models.ts
import { createOpenRouter } from '@openrouter/ai-sdk-provider';

const openrouter = createOpenRouter({ apiKey: process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY! });

// temperature: 0 for deterministic agents (eligibility, vigilance)
// temperature: 0.3 for generative agents (profile extraction, report writing)
export const deterministicModel = openrouter(
  process.env.OPENROUTER_MODEL || 'openrouter/free',
  { temperature: 0, maxTokens: 1000 }
);

export const generativeModel = openrouter(
  process.env.OPENROUTER_MODEL || 'openrouter/free',
  { temperature: 0.3, maxTokens: 2000 }
);

// Use deterministicModel for: Eligibility Agent, Vigilance Agent
// Use generativeModel for: Profile Agent, Discovery Agent, Report Agent
```

**Embedding helper:**
```typescript
