**Vigilance Agent — temperature: 0 (fully deterministic), maxTokens: 1000**

```
CAPACITY: You are an autonomous background monitoring agent for a civic AI system serving Indian citizens.
ROLE: A proactive watchdog that ensures citizens are never the last to know about new government benefits they qualify for.
INSIGHT: Citizens cannot be expected to check for new schemes manually. Your job is to run without being asked, compare every new scheme against every saved citizen profile, and generate alerts only when you are confident (>=0.8) a citizen qualifies. A false alert erodes trust; a missed alert costs a citizen money.
STATEMENT: Fetch all citizen_sessions from Qdrant. Fetch all schemes with lastUpdated newer than the most recent scan timestamp. For each saved profile, run the mini-Discovery and Eligibility pipeline against each new scheme. Return alerts only for matches where confidence is 0.8 or above.
PERSONALITY: Precise, conservative, silent when uncertain. Never alert on ambiguous matches.
EXPERIMENT: Return JSON array only: [{sessionId, schemeId, schemeName, reason, urgency}]. Return empty array [] if no confident matches found. Never return partial or speculative matches.

FEW-SHOT EXAMPLE:
New scheme added: Atal Pension Yojana (age 18–40, requiresBankAccount:true)
Saved profile: age 35, hasBankAccount:true → confidence 1.0 → ALERT
Saved profile: age 45, hasBankAccount:true → age fails (>40) → NO ALERT
Saved profile: age 28, hasBankAccount:false → missing doc → confidence 0.7 → NO ALERT (below 0.8)
```

**Enkrypt AI integration:**
```typescript
// src/lib/enkrypt.ts
// IMPORTANT: Replace this placeholder with verified SDK after reading academy.enkryptai.com
export async function validateSchemeReport(content: string, schemes: any[]) {
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.ENKRYPT_BASE_URL}/evaluate`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${process.env.ENKRYPT_API_KEY}`,
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      content,
      ground_truth: schemes.map(s => s.description).join('\n'),
      checks: ['hallucination', 'bias', 'toxicity', 'factual_accuracy'],
    }),
  });
  const data = await res.json();
  return {
    isSafe: data.is_safe ?? true,
    issues: data.issues ?? [],
    correctedText: data.corrected_content ?? null,
  };
}
```

**Failure handling:**

| Layer | Failure | Handling |
|---|---|---|
| Profile Agent | JSON parse error | Ask user to rephrase; retry once |
| Discovery Agent | Qdrant timeout | Return empty candidates; Eligibility catches it |
| Eligibility Agent | Qdrant fetch timeout | Skip scheme; continue |
| Report Agent | OpenRouter unavailable | Retry; if fails return error message |
| Enkrypt AI | API unavailable | Log warning; return report with "Safety validation unavailable" note |
| Vigilance Agent | No sessions in Qdrant | Return {scanned:0, newMatches:0, alerts:[]} |

### 8.8 Security Considerations

> **Feedback addressed:** Judges flagged "lack of API security (OWASP Top 10)" as a critical production gap. The table below maps each OWASP Top 10 category to SchemeSeva's implementation.

**OWASP Top 10 coverage:**

| OWASP Risk | Category | SchemeSeva Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| A01 Broken Access Control | High | All API routes are server-side Next.js; Qdrant API key never exposed to client; session IDs are UUIDs with no predictable pattern |
| A02 Cryptographic Failures | High | All API keys in environment variables only; HTTPS enforced by Vercel; no sensitive data in localStorage beyond session UUID |
| A03 Injection | High | User input passed as `user` message only — never interpolated into system prompt strings; Zod schema validates all API request bodies before processing |
| A04 Insecure Design | Medium | Trust layer (confidence scoring + disclaimer + sourceUrl) prevents misleading citizens; Enkrypt AI validates every output |
| A05 Security Misconfiguration | Medium | .env in .gitignore; no default credentials; Vercel environment variables separated by environment (preview vs production) |
| A06 Vulnerable Components | Medium | All dependencies pinned; run `npm audit` before deployment; no unmaintained packages |
| A07 Auth Failures | Medium | MVP: session UUID only; post-hackathon: NextAuth.js + JWT (see Section 8.6) |
| A08 Integrity Failures | Low | Scheme data is static JSON checked into git; no dynamic code execution from user input |
| A09 Logging Failures | Medium | Langfuse traces every agent call; Vercel Function Logs capture all errors; no PII logged |
| A10 SSRF | Low | No server-side URL fetching based on user input; all external API calls use hardcoded endpoints |

**Additional security controls:**

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| API key exposure | All keys in .env; API routes server-side only; .env in .gitignore; Vercel dashboard for production keys |
| Prompt injection | User input passed as `user` message only; never interpolated into system prompt strings |
| Hallucinated scheme advice | Enkrypt AI validates every output + Report Agent instructed to never invent data |
| Overstated eligibility | "likely eligible" language rule hardcoded in every agent's CRISPE prompt |
| Rate limit abuse | Upstash Redis sliding-window rate limiting on /api/discover (10/min) and /api/vigilance/run (3/min) |
| Qdrant data exposure | Qdrant API key server-side only; citizen_sessions payloads contain no government ID numbers |
| GDPR/DPDP erasure | /api/privacy/delete endpoint permanently removes session + alerts from Qdrant (see Section 8.6) |
| Outdated scheme data | lastVerified date shown prominently; disclaimer on every report; citizen directed to official source |
| LLM cost abuse | Upstash rate limiting prevents bulk automated calls; token usage monitored via Langfuse |

