### 8.12 Data Governance — GDPR and DPDP Act 2023 Compliance

> **Feedback addressed:** "Lack of GDPR-compliant data governance (right to erasure) for persistent session storage" was flagged as a HIGH priority critical gap.

**What personal data SchemeSeva stores:**

| Data | Where stored | Classification |
|---|---|---|
| CitizenProfile (age, income, occupation, category, state) | Qdrant citizen_sessions | Personal data under DPDP Act 2023 |
| Session UUID | Browser localStorage + Qdrant | Pseudonymous identifier |
| Scheme discovery history (found scheme IDs) | Qdrant citizen_sessions.foundSchemes | Inferred preference data |
| Vigilance alerts | Qdrant pending_alerts | Personal data (sessionId linkable to profile) |

**DPDP Act 2023 and GDPR compliance checklist:**

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Purpose limitation | Data used only for scheme discovery and Vigilance alerts — stated in Privacy Policy |
| Storage limitation | Session data auto-expires in 90 days (Qdrant TTL) post-hackathon |
| Right to erasure | /api/privacy/delete endpoint permanently deletes session + alerts (see Section 8.6) |
| Data minimisation | Only fields needed for eligibility checking are stored; no government ID numbers stored |
| Consent | "Delete my data" link in footer; future: explicit consent checkbox before first profile save |
| Security | Qdrant API key server-side only; data encrypted in transit via HTTPS; no PII in logs |
| Transparency | Privacy Policy link in footer; plain-language description of what is stored and why |

